			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard, monk, cleric trio<a name="43346"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 1 04 7:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>That's a very powerful trio. However, doing hards with 3 is really iffy, no matter how good you are. The problem isn't the danger - with that trio you should be able to take out just about anything - the problem is the time limit. 
<br />

<br />
First off, you do not want adds. You're only going to be able to take out one mob at a time. I hope you're used to doing crowd control while switching targets. Cleric should definitely be ready with root/instill in case mezz fails. 
<br />

<br />
I foresee the cleric going OOM a lot, even if you twist mana song full time.
<br />

<br />
The biggest hurdle I see are going to be the healers. The cleric might be able to get off a stun to interrupt any heal attempts... but it'll be tough, and without nukers or additional melee damage, those healers are going to be huge time-wasters. Is the cleric packing any focus items? Some Spell Haste and some Mana Regen would be very very handy...
<br />

<br />
One thing I've never tried, but I've always wanted to, is using charm in an adventure. (My usual adventure groups are freaked out by the idea of charming an LDoN mob... it's silly.) Charming a mob with each pull gives you additional damage and will cause you to share agro with the monk... sharing hp loss with the monk will reduce your downtime in the long run (you can always twist in HP regen + mana regen during your med breaks.)
<br />

<br />
It really depends on you being on top of your game with your crowd control and the cleric being on top of his game with root/instill and stun.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">"And now for my next miracle, I will turn water... into funk!"
