				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard, monk, cleric trio<a name="43355"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 1 04 8:00 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I trio a lot with my pally and cleric friend.  However, it's getting harder even on the normal as we get closer to the 50s.  
<br />

<br />
I've done a lot of hards, even some without clerics and you need close to a  full group.  I'd say a minumum of 5 for hard and make sure you have a ton of DPS to make sure the cleric isn't having to heal too much.
<br />

<br />
As far as charm goes, if I'm in a trio, charm is much more effective than mez for adds.  It literally adds another attacker to take out the mob first.  It's also effective for handling casters while you hack away at another mob.  Then move the charmed mob away from the group and have it guard or sit.  Then when it breaks, the main tank can pull aggro.  Groups don't usually like charm because they can't instantly attack the mob.  On the other hand, it's great when you have one person that continually breaks mez by not being on the right assist. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">  </span></td>
