			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard, monk, cleric trio<a name="43376"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 1 04 9:31 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I use a combination of Charm and Mez when we're adventuring. I usually aim to pull 3 mobs at a time. The Monk know immediately which one to take, leaving me to charm the 2nd and set it on the 3rd. By the time we've killed the first the other 2 are nice and low so i mezz the 3rd mob when charm breaks and finish both off one at a time. If we get two mobs i flick between either charming the add or mezzing it. I've eventually managed to learn how to beat and twist on one mob whilst keeping the others mezzed. For me that was one of the hardest things to learn for some reason :p
<br />

<br />
As for focus effects we try and keep our tribute topped up, and the cleric uses that for FT and Spell haste. I'm also wearing a <a target="_new" href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=68318">http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=68318</a> (Painted Primal Mask) so i can put Cantana into my regular twist.
<br />

<br />
My main concerns are time and resists. Its not too bad on normal adventures when you get resists as CC is quite easy. However i'm going to get a lot more resists and critical resists on hard, and with mobs hitting a lot harder i'm going to get chewed up quickly. The time element is self-explanatory.
<br />

<br />
Has anyone managed to trio a High risk LDoN, and if so how did you do it?
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
