			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard, monk, cleric trio<a name="43392"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 1 04 11:46 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The only thing that really matters, assuming you're twinked is your mez/charm ceiling. If you do a hard, I doubt the mobs will be in your mez limit. As you get higher level, I can guarantee you won't and depending which missions you're pulling, you just won't be successful. I use mez all the time to interrupt casters, mez mobs, and I use the charm thing but once you're above level 51 it's really hard to be successful.
<br />

<br />
Bottom line is anyways, in a 3 man group. I use either warrior/cleric/me or rogue/cleric/me. I'm fully capable of tanking the mobs in a normal mission and in a normal mission, you can charm and mez very easily which just makes it that much faster. Essentially, it's worth it to do normals only and not hards, as I haven't been extremely impressed with the drops or xp in hards in relation to the danger and potential hazards. You can try a hard with 3, and I have but have failed and I consider myself extremely skilled. Let me know how you do but my thoughts are unless you've spent over 200k in equip on both the monk and bard, your dps is going to be junk in a hard and casters will be uncontrollable.
<br />

<br />
As far as mana regen is concerned. Just make sure your cleric gets a KEI and the two of you get a virtue before you go in. If your cleric uses only CHeal like any good cleric should (assuming you guys know how to control agro) then he won't have any issues with mana. My buddy 2 boxes either the cleric/war or the cleric/rogue and when I'm bored I'll add in my beastlord or my other rogue on my 2nd box to pound through missions. 
<br />

<br />
Good luck... you'll need it. Especially after your avg level is 54</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
