				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard, monk, cleric trio<a name="43441"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 1 04 2:11 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Resists &amp; crit resists.. you will have resists on lull, no question. How's your CHA? If you can get your CHA above 200, you shouldn't see too much of a problem with crit resists. Get a Grandmaster's Trophy if you can.
<br />

<br />
And with smart lulling, you can mitigate how many adds there are on a crit resist. Between a high CHA and a strong pulling technique (there's a really good pulling guide for hard LDoN here) getting more than 2 adds on a pull should be an extreme rarity.
<br />

<br />
As for the time issue, I don't think I can say anything else that hasn't been said, other than it's going to be really tough. I'd actually really like to know how you fare.
<br />

<br />
BTW, in response to this:
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">
<br />
If your cleric uses only CHeal like any good cleric should (assuming you guys know how to control agro) then he won't have any issues with mana.
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I hope you're talking about CELESTIAL Heal rather than COMPLETE Heal. =) Celestial is going to be much more mana efficient at level 45 than complete.
<br />

<br />
Even then, I hope the cleric is doing more than just healing. If he's not rooting &amp; stunning, he's as bad as a one-hit-wonder.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
