				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard, monk, cleric trio<a name="43703"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 2 04 12:19 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well we started one last night, just to get a 'feel' for what is going to be needed........ and <b>d*mn!</b> those mobs are hard<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
For buffs all we had on was Virtue and kei, and thought we'd go see what it was like. We decided on a NRo one as they seem to be easier.
<br />

<br />
I started with a room with 5 mobs, 3 of which we're casters. Firing up track mobs varied from con'ing Dark Blue through to Yellow, so I started lulling and was pleasently surprised at getting no resists (130 cha) and pulled the nearest one.
<br />

<br />
All in all we spent 15 minutes in the zone and killed 5 mobs. The good news is that none of us died, but I was managing to get single pulls every time so didn't get a chance to find out how reliable my mez would be on the even and yellow con's.
<br />
I decided against trying charm, as we wanted to see how our dps was without it (and from what i've seen you can't charm yellow mobs without the relevant AA).
<br />

<br />
After those 5 mobs our cleric lost his bottle and wanted to leave and do a normal one, so we had to abandon it. HOWEVER, we went back to the same dungeon to start a normal adventure, and found the mobs to be a lot tougher than they have been during previous adventures(our group average has risen slightly). In fact the mobs we're only dropping slightly quicker than the High Risk adv. We completed the adventure in about 65 minutes with only one death due to weird warping and a BIG train. Hehe, there are times that I wished we got Fade as a lvl 1 innate ability, but i digress<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
After completion we we're discussing things and concluded that it <b>may</b> be possible to complete a High Risk adv with this trio, albeit with a little skill and a LOT of luck. The Cleric is willing to give it a try after a little subtle persuation (we've got some very compromising photo's of him...  :lol).
<br />

<br />
We're gonna give it a real go on Sunday, as i'm working evenings until then. I shall post here with our result afterwards, and will either be elated or humbled<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
